# Cursor Rules for Alonso's Website

## Package Manager
- Use PNPM instead of npm/yarn
- Always use `pnpm` commands for package management

## Terminal Tools
- Prefer Rust-based tools when available:
  - Use `bat` instead of `cat`
  - Use `exa` instead of `ls`
  - Use `fd` instead of `find`
  - Use `ripgrep` instead of `grep`
  - Use `dust` instead of `du`
  - Use `procs` instead of `ps`

## Code Style
- Keep code simple and readable
- Minimize custom code, maximize reusable components
- Use modern web standards
- Prefer functional programming patterns

## Project Structure
- Keep it lightweight and fast
- No unnecessary frameworks or dependencies
- Focus on performance and simplicity
